OL,3,CHeadteacher launches knife crime
OL,4,Clessons after son's fatal stabbing
OL,6,F"Knife crime is in the news nearly
OL,7,Fevery day the children go online, they
OL,8,Flisten to rappers who sing songs about
OL,9,Fit, it's part of their lives, it's not
OL,10,Fsomething we can shield them from.
OL,11,FIt's not to scare them, it's to
OL,12,Feducate them."
OL,14,FYear six pupils are being taught about
OL,15,Fthe potential prison sentences facing
OL,16,Fanyone involved in knife crime and the
OL,17,Feffect on the families of victims and
OL,18,Fcriminals.
OL,20,FEleven-year-olds Leonard and Amelia
OL,21,Fsay the lessons have had an impact.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
