OL,3,CHeadteacher launches knife crime
OL,4,Clessons after son's fatal stabbing
OL,6,F"I know that if I do knife crime, I
OL,7,Fwon't be able to play football because
OL,8,FI'll go to prison. I'm never ever
OL,9,Fgoing to carry a knife," Leonard said.
OL,11,FAmelia said: "We are not too young to
OL,12,Flearn about knives, we are the right
OL,13,Fage. If you stab someone you will
OL,14,Fnever get a job and you'll go to
OL,15,Fprison."
OL,17,FDanny Castledine had been on a night
OL,18,Fin Amsterdam when he lost contact with
OL,19,Fa friend and was attacked.
